Text.Value: You ready your weapon, I will ready my spells.
Losiir. I see you've earned your robes.
May the wounds you inflict match those of my blade!
With your sword and my patron's fey magic, we will prevail.
My patron knows of these creatures - we shall slay them with ease.
We shall cast them into the void.
Tsk'va. The parasite has already taken hold. We must take to a crèche and be cleansed.
We're in Avernus. First of the Nine Hells.
Attack.
Yes, we risk turning into mind flayers. But purification will have to wait until we take control of the ship.
We need to get rid of them and seek out the helm.
Then you'll understand why we must leave at once.
Very well - if you are fit to lead, our victory will be the proof!
In Queen Vlaakith's name!
For the light!
I will make a most decadent sacrifice of these creatures.
They stand in the way of the divine's will - they must be slain.
Then unleash it upon these infernal minions!
Close your eyes. Breathe deep. Prepare to fight.
I need no weapon. My veins flow with arcane power.
Imps? Where are we?
The hunt begins... You lead, I'll cover you.
Prepare your instrument.
Another survivor. We may yet see an end to this torment.
After you.
I know this place. We are in Avernus, first of the Nine Hells.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Players move into position for combat. Gith guide and player in parallel.

Text.Value: Make them tremble with your music's fury!
But first, we must get to the helm.
Ready your weapon.
We are spotted! Prepare yourself.
Let us see what a soldier of Crèche K'liir can do.
Steel yourself and follow me.
Nature's might is always ready.
I'll pick them off from the shadows. They won't even know I was there.
Lae'zel - you still live! May the Queen's favour be yours.
ROAR!
Htak'a!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player moves into position for combat. Player in the lead.

Text.Value: Good. Now go, and make every strike count!
On my oath - let us slay these foul creatures.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] REUSE: The Still_Peace + lookAt for his head turn. the same node/reaction is needed in the TUT_LowerDeck_AfterImpFight. If the lookAt doesn't workwell, a custom can be made from that same Still_Peace asset.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Imps scavenging around corpses look up.

Text.Value: By Vlaakith's touch, what is this?
So they put a parasite in your eye, too?
No - forget it. We must ready ourselves for battle. There are imps blocking our path.
Mark your prey, and we will split them open!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player moves into position for combat. Gith guide leads.

Text.Value: Follow my lead.
*Your head throbs and your skin tingles. Visions rush past: a dragon's wing, a silver sword - and a flash of your face seen through the gith man's eyes.*
*Your head throbs and your skin tingles. Visions rush past: a dragon's wing, a silver sword - and a flash of your face seen through the strange man's eyes.*
My weapon is always ready.
What's at the helm?
It's where we gain control over the ship. We must travel the planes - leave Avernus, before these imps tear us apart.

Synopsis: Gith Guide encourages player to get to the helm. Has a mindmeld with the player but brushes it aside.
